{"tid":1072782,"cid":5,"subCid":0,"title":"Tesla前中國員工偷自動駕駛資料 然後辭職去阿里旗下小鵬汽車打工 tesla起訴","createTime":"2019-03-22T08:32:18.000Z","updateTime":"2019-03-24T17:50:10.000Z","uid":48083,"like":58,"dislike":1,"uniUserReply":38,"replies":[{"pid":"64daf485f42ba3dbda25d2cd617d727a06535ef8","tid":1072782,"uid":48083,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-03-22T08:32:18.000Z","msg":"Tesla today sued ex-employee Guangzhi Cao for allegedly stealing the source code for the leccy car maker's Autopilot software.<br />\n<br />\nThe lawsuit, filed in a US federal district court in Silicon Valley, claims Cao began looking for a new job in November 2018, and received a verbal offer from China-based &quot;Tesla imitator&quot; Xiaopeng Motors Technology Company Ltd (XMotors or Xpeng Motors) before the end of the month. Prior to his departure from Tesla on January 3, 2019, the software and hardware engineer uploaded source code related to Autopilot to his Apple iCloud account, it is claimed.<br />\n<br />\n&quot;Long before he left, <span style=\"color: red;\"><span style=\"font-size: large;\"><strong>Cao began uploading complete copies of Tesla&rsquo;s Autopilot-related source code to his personal iCloud account &ndash; more than 300,000 files and directories, in violation of Tesla&rsquo;s policies and its agreements with Cao,&quot; the complaint stated.<br />\n<br />\n&quot;Then, as he was looking to leave Tesla, Cao created .zip files of Tesla&rsquo;s complete Autopilot-related source code repositories, making them smaller and easier to move.&quot;</strong></span></span><br />\n<br />\nThe complaint contends Cao received a written job offer from XMotors on December 12, and thereafter deleted 120,000 files from his iCloud and disconnected the cloud storage service from his Tesla-issued computer on December 26. And in the days leading up to his departure, it's claimed, Cao logged onto Tesla's secure network repeatedly, and then cleared his browser history before he left.<br />\n<br />\nCao, the lawsuit stated, is one of only about 40 employees out of 45,000 granted access to Tesla's neural-network source code, used to build the super-cruise-control Autopilot product, and one of about 200 with access to the broader set of Autopilot source."},{"pid":"389dad11f56a526f63a0603671746fbb051820d3","tid":1072782,"uid":48083,"like":47,"dislike":0,"score":47,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-03-22T08:32:36.000Z","msg":"IP wars<br />\n<br />\nAccording to the company, Autopilot has taken more than five years to develop, at a cost of hundreds of millions of dollars.<br />\n<br />\nT<span style=\"color: red;\"><span style=\"font-size: large;\">esla claims at least five of its employees have</span></span> left and taken jobs at XMotors, including Cao. Its complaint points out that the FBI last year collared former Apple employee Xiaolang Zhang, who was allegedly headed for a job in China at XMotors after downloading self-driving car hardware schematics from Apple.<br />\n<br />\nTesla is suing under the Defend Trade Secrets Act, a law approved in 2016 by then President Obama to address long standing concerns about economic espionage, as well as the California Uniform Trade Secrets Act. It also alleges breach of contract.<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.theregister.co.uk/2019/03/21/tesla_sues_former_employee/\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theregister.co.uk%2F2019%2F03%2F21%2Ftesla_sues_former_employee%2F&d=nGD0VYfdVRVKlmm%2FccroEw9axkDoCoA19ZsVt7gViHY%3D&h=73ed233d\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.theregister.co.uk/2019/03/21/tesla_sues_former_employee/</a><br />\n<br />\n<br />\n仲走入去開廠<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/angel.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/angel.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/angel.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"893a914b697fcf9ca3cbae887a390c1e04c1c08a","tid":1072782,"uid":61018,"like":16,"dislike":0,"score":16,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-03-22T08:32:57.000Z","msg":"不意外"},{"pid":"2176d92236720cbd8a6a1706fea972679d384ed7","tid":1072782,"uid":76063,"like":24,"dislike":0,"score":24,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-03-22T08:33:19.000Z","msg":"係大陸告得入?"},{"pid":"5d111614844c54cad469ba29de35a28a82a669e0","tid":1072782,"uid":1988,"like":49,"dislike":0,"score":49,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-03-22T08:33:29.000Z","msg":"都未開始run 就已經俾人偷野<img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/hehe.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"69a147e703b9ef63a2bf315a298e599bd8816148","tid":1072782,"uid":2383,"like":0,"dislike":1,"score":-1,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-03-22T08:33:49.000Z","msg":"支那人<img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/hehe.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"f198adbab8b8e4636c8f6d1e40eb9d0f1c694a00","tid":1072782,"uid":48083,"like":15,"dislike":0,"score":15,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-03-22T08:33:57.000Z","msg":"Apple都中<br />\n<br />\n跳槽到小鵬汽車的前 Apple 工程師在試圖離開美國時被捕<br />\n<br />\n此人已承認竊取了 Apple 的自駕車機密，但小鵬表示自己並不知情。<br />\n<br />\n當所有廠商都想在自動駕駛這個新興市場中分一杯羹的時候，各種商業間諜行為層出不窮，也就不是什麼好奇怪的事了。據彭博社報導，一位名叫張小浪的 Apple 前工程師，在 7 月 7 日試圖離開美國飛往中國時被捕。此事發生之前，張小浪被 Apple 指控竊取了跟其自駕車計畫有關的商業機密（包括設計圖、技術資料、電路板和伺服器）。而在六月末接受 FBI 調查時，張小浪也承認自己的確有將公司資料下載到妻子的電腦上，以便自己在離開 Apple 後仍能對這些內容加以利用。<br />\n<br />\n至於具體是要怎麼個利用法，自然還有待調查進一步展開。不過張小浪在今年四月回中國休完陪產假後，就曾告知 Apple 自己準備離職回國，跳槽去新創公司小鵬汽車工作。當時 Apple 內部的監察部門就意識到了潛在的竊密可能性，張小浪的主管也發現其在休假時登入公司內網的頻率有所升高，而且本應在中國的張小浪期間居然也曾在總部出現。<br />\n<br />\n在事發之後，事件涉及到的另一方小鵬汽車也在第一時間發佈了聲明。他們強調張小浪在五月入職時簽署了智財權合規文件，而且「沒有記錄顯示他向小鵬汽車上報任何敏感和違規的情況」。另外小鵬目前也已按照規定封存了張小浪的電腦和辦公用品，未來將「積極配合」相關調查。而 Apple 這邊則已經明確表示，自己會「竭盡所能確保張小浪和其它涉及該案者被繩之以法」。<br />\n<br />\n話說，最近美國國內對中國公司竊取美國技術的指責聲浪越來越高，張小浪這件事出來以後，估計又會引發新一輪的熱議吧...<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://chinese.engadget.com/2018/07/11/apple-employee-accused-self-driving-secret-theft/\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fchinese.engadget.com%2F2018%2F07%2F11%2Fapple-employee-accused-self-driving-secret-theft%2F&d=nGD0VYfdVRVKlmm%2FccroEw9axkDoCoA19ZsVt7gViHY%3D&h=f3682990\" target=\"_blank\">https://chinese.engadget.com/2018/07/11/apple-employee-accused-self-driving-secret-theft/</a>"},{"pid":"42b77e1b7b9ca9afbaeadbbcfc6e4b516d374f04","tid":1072782,"uid":81113,"like":50,"dislike":0,"score":50,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2019-03-22T08:34:06.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"https://na.cx/i/tvF4NkT.gif\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fna.cx%2Fi%2FtvF4NkT.gif&h=1d7a554f&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n<br />\n<span style=\"font-size: xx-large;\">請中國員工？</span>"},{"pid":"7abb6c301bb33a5abef214b5f264ce11b6ab6b5a","tid":1072782,"uid":40470,"like":8,"dislike":2,"score":6,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-03-22T08:34:20.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/hehe.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <br />\n<br />\n抵死啦<br />\n<br />\n當買個教訓<br />\n<br />\n希望你知道以後應該點對付中國人"},{"pid":"fe86bd452c447b3ab719bfb06c4e9a875f278623","tid":1072782,"uid":54754,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-03-22T08:34:25.000Z","msg":"符合蟈情<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/angel.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"941ca33e82073a15ea92b0a707ecc0a417a46e9c","tid":1072782,"uid":48083,"like":8,"dislike":0,"score":8,"quote":{"pid":"42b77e1b7b9ca9afbaeadbbcfc6e4b516d374f04","tid":1072782,"uid":81113,"like":50,"dislike":0,"score":50,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2019-03-22T08:34:06.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"https://na.cx/i/tvF4NkT.gif\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fna.cx%2Fi%2FtvF4NkT.gif&h=1d7a554f&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n<br />\n<span style=\"font-size: xx-large;\">請中國員工？</span>"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-03-22T08:34:31.000Z","msg":"全撚部賊嚟"},{"pid":"70d31c879ee9b5b597ce2279c946ff451ac5fbfa","tid":1072782,"uid":7369,"like":18,"dislike":0,"score":18,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-03-22T08:36:10.000Z","msg":"告乜撚嘢呀, 你去大陸開廠同雙手送晒d技術畀大陸有鳩分別咩!"},{"pid":"20f6758e29972ffec7401c4e5be414c44a56a1ef","tid":1072782,"uid":23993,"like":31,"dislike":0,"score":31,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2019-03-22T08:36:17.000Z","msg":"Elon Musk太睇少支那種嘅無恥程度啦<br />\n仲要係上海開gigafactory 實同apple一樣俾支那